subsection.def:
the term “Contracting Party” or “Party”
                        means France or the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, as the context
                        requires;

the term “person” includes an
                        individual, a company and any other body of
                        persons;

the term “company” means any
                        body corporate or any entity which is treated as a body corporate for tax
                        purpose;

the term “enterprise”
                        applies to the carrying on of any
                        business;

subparagraph.content:
in the case of France, the Minister in charge of finance or his
                                authorised
                                representative;

subsection.content:
a mine, an oil or gas well, a quarry or any other place of
                            extraction of natural
                            resources;

section.leadIn:
An enterprise shall be deemed to have a permanent establishment in a
                    Contracting Party and to carry on business through that permanent establishment
                    if:

paragraph.content:
the use of facilities solely for the purpose of storage, display,
                            or delivery of goods or merchandise belonging to the
                            enterprise;

the maintenance of a stock of goods or merchandise belonging to the
                            enterprise solely for the purpose of storage, display or
                            delivery;

the maintenance of a stock of goods or merchandise belonging to the
                            enterprise solely for the purpose of processing by another
                            enterprise;

subparagraph.content:
on a loan directly or indirectly financed or guaranteed by the Hong
                            Kong Monetary
                            Authority;

paragraph.content:
alienated or exchanged in the framework of a reorganisation of a
                            company, a merger, a scission or a similar operation;
                            or

subsection.content:
the remuneration is paid by, or on behalf of, an employer who is not a
                        resident of the other Party;
                        and

the remuneration is not borne by a permanent establishment which the
                        employer has in the other Party;
                        and

paragraph.content:
in the case of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, has the
                            right of abode therein and in the case of France, is a national thereof;
                            or

subsection.content:
to carry out administrative measures at variance with the laws and
                        administrative practice of that or of the other Contracting
                        Party;

to supply information which is not obtainable under the laws or in the
                        normal course of the administration of that or of the other Contracting
                        Party;

subparagraph.content:
in respect of taxes on income withheld at source, for amounts
                            taxable after the calendar year in which the Agreement enters into
                            force;

in respect of the other taxes, for taxation the taxable event of
                            which will occur after the calendar year in which the Agreement enters
                            into force;

in respect of taxes on income withheld at source, for amounts
                            taxable after the calendar year in which the notice of termination is
                            given;

paragraph.content:
any individual who ordinarily resides in the Hong Kong Special
